donkeypong/wide-and-wonderful-waterfalls.title: Wide and Wonderful Waterfalls
donkeypong/wide-and-wonderful-waterfalls.body:
![Mocona.jpg](https://steemitimages.com/DQmeou7stKCq9BayNmcTf4MiuTd1zXV7QcUh32H725nQA82/Mocona.jpg)

Waterfalls are one of nature’s greatest wonders. I love water in many of its natural forms (lakes, oceans, rivers, creeks), but nothing is so violent and yet so peaceful as a waterfall. Everyone loves tall waterfalls, but the wide ones are a visual treat. 

Recently, scientists told us that the English Channel was once spanned by a land bridge, made from the same chalky material as the White Cliffs of Dover. 450,000 years ago, when a glacial lake burst, the channel was flooded. For a time, this land bridge became a gigantic waterfall.

![Land Bridge.jpg](https://steemitimages.com/DQmP1V5PcuDHvubZoNjzgxKGYFriZTh2RzFtjYUysCYDeTh/Land%20Bridge.jpg)

The waterfall was as high as 350 feet (106 meters) tall. But its most amazing feature was its length: 20 miles (32 kilometers) long! Of course, that was really its width, not its length. The waterfall was spilling over the land bridge all the way from Britain to Fra

ericvancewalton/things-that-will-bring-y.body:
<center> ![](https://media.giphy.com/media/qwiCNHIKMDNjq/giphy.gif) </center>

---



**T**he elusive, “writing zone” is a small bandwidth of consciousness that exists in the creative mind when we’re at our peak of creativity.  For our creativity to be at its peak we must be as healthy, in both body and mind, as we can be. We’ve all read about the well-documented exploits of famous writers and how they regularly used drugs, alcohol, and even caffeine to ignite their spark of creativity but this almost never has a good final outcome. I’ve found there are many positive and healthy choices that writers can make to enhance our creativity without the negative repercussions.  

# “It’s none of their business that you have to learn to write. Let them think you were born that way.” – Ernest Hemingway #

Have you ever been at a point in your life where you feel like you are overthinking things? 

Perhaps you are just a person in general that tends to over think? You like to look at things from every angle, put yourself in everyone else's shoes, and try to predict all the possible outcomes in a given situation.

Does that sound like you at all?

Well, sometimes that is a great ability to have, but sometimes it is not...

https://s23.postimg.org/3otbnskbv/e3efbe832b6d49e3fa41ff3e76a0721a.jpg

Let me tell you a little story about my favorite sports team that helps drive home that point.

thecryptofiend/common-painkillers-increa.title: Common Painkillers Increase the Risk of Heart Attacks
thecryptofiend/common-painkillers-increa.body:
![ThinkstockPhotos-525299581.jpg](https://steemitimages.com/DQmRRmBm949oMxfZTb2iVi923GHwV1k628nHCXd5DZ72nPe/ThinkstockPhotos-525299581.jpg) ___

Introduction

___

A recent meta-analysis study in the British Medical Journal [1] suggests that using NSAIDs (a commonly prescribed type of painkiller) increases the risk of acute myocardial infarction (heart attack).

This study is open access and you can read (or download) it [here](http://www.bmj.com/content/357/bmj.j1909). ___

What is new here?

___

Not much to be honest. It was already known that NSAIDs increase the risk of MI (heart attacks).

![ThinkstockPhotos-481787538.jpg](https://steemitimages.com/DQmQVjiih9LgTCfSeHxb7hUCuFDqXYaYDi3cKAeNgTzFqTr/ThinkstockPhotos-481787538.jpg)
